quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,88,"And [Allāh acknowledges] his saying,{1} ",footnotes:1:i.e., the complaint of Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) about his people.
  43,89,"So turn aside from them and say, ",footnotes:1:Meaning safety or security, i.e., "I will not harm you."  This was before permission was granted for armed struggle.
  50,13,"And ʿAad and Pharaoh and the brothers [i.e., people] of Lot"
  50,14,"And the companions of the thicket and the people of Tubbaʿ. All denied the messengers, so My threat was justly fulfilled."
  50,15,"Did We fail in the first creation? But they are in confusion over a new creation."
  51,7,"By the heaven containing pathways,{1}",footnotes:1:Explained as tracks, layers or orbits.
  51,8,"Indeed, you are in differing speech.{1}",footnotes:1:About Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) and the Qur’ān.
  51,9,"Deluded away from it [i.e., the Qur’ān] is he who is deluded."